---

<section class="section section--compact" id="fractional-cfo-proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>4&times;</b> Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>CFO-level</b> finance &amp; modeling</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Fixed-fee</b> written scope, first</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>1 business day</b> response</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><span class="proof-strip__rating">5.0</span> 2 verified Clutch reviews</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What a fractional CFO actually delivers.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A fractional CFO is an experienced finance executive serving as a part-time Chief Financial Officer for businesses that need strategic financial leadership but aren&rsquo;t yet ready for a full-time CFO hire. The work spans six areas: financial strategy, cash-flow forecasting (13-week rolling cash flow, scenario modeling, runway analysis), board and investor reporting, fundraising support, KPI and unit economics, and senior advisory (strategic decisions, pricing, hiring economics, M&amp;A readiness).</p>
      <p>TechBrot accepts a limited number of fractional CFO engagements per quarter, delivered through senior operators on a fixed monthly retainer of $3,000&ndash;$8,000+. Most engagements pair with <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping</a> and <a href="/accounting/payroll-management/?intent=payroll">payroll</a> underneath &mdash; CFO-level work only delivers value on top of accurate operational books. Coordinates with your CPA or EA; does not include tax filing, audit, legal, or investment-advisory services.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fractional CFO, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is it time?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these describe where you are, the answer is probably yes.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-coverage">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What we cover. What we don&rsquo;t.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in coverage %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ c.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in c.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3>What a fractional CFO is not.</h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ notList | safe }}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-model">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement model</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How a fractional CFO engagement actually runs.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">A defined operating cadence &mdash; weekly rhythm, monthly close, quarterly strategy, and event-driven bursts &mdash; not ad-hoc calls when something breaks.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in engagementModel %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed monthly retainer, defined scope, no hourly billing.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Three tiers by intensity; scope and retainer flex during event-driven windows (fundraising, M&amp;A, audits). Engagements typically pair with bookkeeping and payroll underneath.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong>{{ t.per | safe }}</p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=fractional-cfo">{{ t.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-economics">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why fractional, not full-time</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The economics of CFO work between $1M and $50M.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A full-time CFO at a U.S. business between $1M and $50M revenue typically costs $250,000 to $400,000 fully loaded &mdash; base, bonus, equity, benefits, employer taxes, recruiting, severance reserve. That&rsquo;s before an office, an analyst to support the CFO, or the accounting software the CFO will demand.</p>
      <p>Most businesses in this range don&rsquo;t need 40 hours a week of CFO work. They need 20 to 60 hours a month of senior strategic work, delivered consistently. The remaining 30+ hours of a full-time CFO&rsquo;s week gets absorbed by operational tasks better handled by a controller, a bookkeeper, or software &mdash; at a fraction of the cost.</p>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>The fractional CFO model isn&rsquo;t a discount &mdash; it&rsquo;s a <strong>match</strong>. Senior judgment for the decisions that need senior judgment; operational accounting for the work that doesn&rsquo;t. Fractional delivers senior strategic work at <strong>15&ndash;30% of full-time cost</strong> &mdash; and when TechBrot runs the bookkeeping underneath, the CFO works from clean books instead of building them.</p>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-profiles">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who it fits</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The business profiles where fractional CFO works.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for p in profiles %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ p.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-onboarding">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Onboarding</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From application to first board meeting.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for s in onboarding %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <p class="num">0{{ loop.index }}</p>
      <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      <p class="prose"><strong>{{ s.sub | safe }}</strong></p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-stack">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The finance stack</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">CFO work only delivers value on accurate books.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The first thing a fractional CFO does on a new engagement is assess the operational accounting underneath. If the books are unreliable &mdash; uncategorized transactions, unreconciled accounts, missing payroll integration, a sloppy chart of accounts &mdash; the CFO must either fix the books first (slow and expensive at CFO rates) or produce analysis on a foundation that can&rsquo;t be trusted (worse).</p>
      <p>TechBrot offers fractional CFO precisely because we already operate the bookkeeping layer cleanly. Engagements that pair fractional CFO with TechBrot <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">bookkeeping</a>, <a href="/accounting/payroll-management/?intent=payroll">payroll</a>, and <a href="/accounting/sales-tax-compliance/?intent=sales-tax">sales tax</a> underneath deliver more value &mdash; the CFO works from accurate books from day one, integration costs disappear, and the finance stack runs as one system instead of three vendors. The pairing isn&rsquo;t required, but when CFO and bookkeeping run together, the math gets simpler.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who runs your CFO engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A senior operator. Named. Accountable.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Fractional CFO engagements are delivered by senior operators with prior experience as full-time CFOs, controllers, or strategic finance leaders at U.S. growth-stage businesses. Engagements are matched on industry, stage, and engagement type &mdash; not on availability. Platform-level engagement review backs every engagement, and the operator who runs it is your named CFO: they show up to your board meetings, talk to your investors, and own the work. Continuity is structurally guaranteed if anything ever needs to transition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-intake">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Scope a fractional CFO engagement.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Tell us the basics and a Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day with next steps and a written scope. Prefer the full intake? The <a href="/contact/?intent=fractional-cfo">complete contact form</a> captures every detail.</p>
    </header>
    {%- set intakePrefix = "fcfo" %}
    {%- set intakeFormId = "fractional-cfo-intake-form" %}
    {%- set intakeIntent = "fractional-cfo" %}
    {%- set intakeSourceType = "bofu-conversion" %}
    {%- set intakeFunnelStage = "BOFU" %}
    {%- set intakeLegend = "What we should look at" %}
    {%- set intakeNote = "Fractional CFO is the common reason businesses reach this page &mdash; add anything else you want scoped in the same call." %}
    {%- set intakeConsent = "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this fractional CFO inquiry." %}
    {%- set intakeSubmit = "Send the Discovery Brief" %}
    {%- set intakeReassurance = "No spam, no list, no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." %}
    {% include "partials/intake-form.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="fractional-cfo-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">CFO questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="fractional-cfo-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="fractional-cfo-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="fractional-cfo-next">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Connected work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What fractional CFO connects to.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
